A passenger killed when a light aircraft crashed in a flaming wreck yesterday afternoon only went up in the plane after a chance offer while visiting an airfield, according to local reports.

They say the 'family man' had not been intending to fly. But after accepting an offer, he died along with the plane's pilot when their Yak 52 aircraft came down near the village of North Weald in Essex.

The passenger was named as father-of-one and flying enthusiast Simon Chamberlain.

