Chef Mark Reynolds saw the incident 
unfold while he was taking his break outside the nearby Fox and Goose 
pub and rushed to help.

He said: 'We were watching the plane doing an aerobatic display over the fields. It was very impressive.

'We
 kept saying the plane was very low in the air and the next thing it 
nose nose-dived into the ground, completely vertical, and burst in to 
