'It was surreal, we started running towards it to see if we could help anyone.

'It was quite a way off. When we got to the plane it was engulfed in flames. He was very badly burned.'

Mr Reynolds, 47, added: 'It was like something you see in a movie. It was very disturbing, something that will stay with me.'

